# Introduction
This report details the fitting of a Hodgkin-Huxley-style action potential model to experimental electrophysiology data.  
The analysis was performed using Julia.  

This document presents the results from two main workflows:
1. Fitting individual *Thamnophis* muscle traces  
2. A comprehensive group analysis comparing different experimental conditions  

---

# Setup Cell: Load packages and helper modules
```julia; echo=false
# Setup and Data Loading
# This cell loads all necessary packages, helper files, and the main dataset.

using Dates, Printf, DataFrames, CSV, Plots, StatsPlots, MixedModels, CategoricalArrays, LaTeXStrings, Statistics, Markdown, Images
using FileIO, PNGFiles

cd(@__DIR__) # Ensure we're in the script directory

include("config.jl")
include("ActionPotential.jl")
include("action_potential_plots.jl") # Using your new filename
using .ActionPotentialModel
using .ActionPotentialPlots

# Create a directory for new images if it doesn't exist
const images_dir = joinpath(pwd(), "report_images")
mkpath(images_dir)

# Define the path to the group analysis results
group_data_path = joinpath(output_folder, "Group_Trace", "latest", "All_sim_data.csv")
species = "Atratus"
group_names_for_report = ["WT", "P", "EPN"]
trace_files = ["$(species)_WT.csv", "$(species)_P.csv", "$(species)_EPN.csv"]

# Load the main dataset and prepare it for analysis
sim_data = if isfile(group_data_path)
    println("Loading group analysis data from: ", group_data_path)
    df = CSV.read(group_data_path, DataFrame)
    
    # Ensure string group names are assigned for plotting
    if !("group" in names(df)) && ("group_id" in names(df))
        df.group = [group_names_for_report[id] for id in df.group_id]
    end
    df; # return the loaded and processed dataframe
else
    println("WARNING: Group analysis data not found at '$(group_data_path)'. Please run the 'group' workflow first.")
    nothing # return nothing if the file is not found
end
```

---

# Model Kinetics
The fundamental behavior of the model is determined by the voltage-dependent kinetics of the ion channel subunits (*m, h,* and *n*).  

The plots below visualize the steady-state activation/inactivation probabilities (`m_infty, h_infty, n_infty`)  
and their corresponding time constants (`tau_m, tau_h, tau_n`) as a function of membrane potential.  

## Steady-state Kinetics

These curves are generated using the average fitted parameters for the WT group.

```julia; echo=false
# Generate plots for subunit kinetics
if sim_data !== nothing
    # Calculate average parameters
    avg_params_by_group = combine(groupby(sim_data, :group), names(sim_data, Real) .=> mean)

    for group_name in group_names_for_report
        avg_params_df = filter(row -> row.group == group_name, avg_params_by_group)

        #display(Markdown.MD(Markdown.parse("### Steady-state Kinetics for Group: `$group_name`\n")))
        
        if !isempty(avg_params_df)
            calculated_means = NamedTuple(avg_params_df[1, :])
            full_avg_params = merge(par_0, calculated_means)
            
            kinetics_fig = ActionPotentialPlots.plot_subunit_kinetics(full_avg_params, "$(group_name) Average")
            kinetics_path = joinpath(images_dir, "subunit_kinetics.png")
            savefig(kinetics_fig, kinetics_path)

            display(kinetics_fig)
        else
            println("*Could not find $(group_name) group data to generate kinetics plot.*")
        end
    end
else
    println("*Group analysis data is missing, skipping kinetics plot.*")
end
```

## Decomposition Plots

These continured plots give current and conductance decomposition

```julia; echo=false
# Generate plots for decomposition plots
if sim_data !== nothing
    # Calculate average parameters
    avg_params_by_group = combine(groupby(sim_data, :group), names(sim_data, Real) .=> mean)

    for group_name in group_names_for_report

        wt_avg_params_df = filter(row -> row.group == group_name, avg_params_by_group)

        file_path = joinpath(data_folder, "$(species)_$(group_name).csv")
        df_raw = CSV.read(file_path, DataFrame; header=4)
        trace = collect(skipmissing(df_raw[:, 2]))
        time = collect(skipmissing(df_raw[:, 1]))
        
        if !isempty(wt_avg_params_df)
            #display(Markdown.MD(Markdown.parse("### Current Decomposition for Group: `$group_name`\n")))
            
            calculated_means = NamedTuple(wt_avg_params_df[1, :])
            full_avg_params = merge(par_0, calculated_means)

            ap = ActionPotentialModel.ActionPotential(full_avg_params, trace, time)
            
            currents_fig = ActionPotentialPlots.plot_currents(ap, group_name)
            currents_path = joinpath(images_dir, "$(group_name)_current_decomposition.png")
            savefig(currents_fig, currents_path)

            display(currents_fig)

            #display(Markdown.MD(Markdown.parse("### Conductance Decomposition for Group: `$group_name`\n")))

            conductances_fig = ActionPotentialPlots.plot_conductances(ap, group_name)
            conductances_path = joinpath(images_dir, "$(group_name)_conductance_decomposition.png")
            savefig(conductances_fig, conductances_path)

            display(conductances_fig)
        else
            println("*Could not find $(group_name) group data to generate decomposition plots.*")
        end 
    end
else
    println("*Group analysis data is missing, skipping decomposition plot.*")
end
```

